## Real-World Scenarios

### Example 20: Process User Data

```javascript
const csv = `id,name,email,signup_date,subscription_active,monthly_spend
1,Alice Johnson,alice@example.com,2023-01-15,true,29.99
2,"Smith, Bob",bob@example.com,2023-06-20,false,0.00
3,Charlie Brown,charlie@example.com,2023-03-10,true,9.99
4,Diana Prince,diana@example.com,2023-02-28,true,49.99
5,"Williams, Eve",eve@example.com,2023-07-05,false,0.00`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Active subscribers
const active = result.filter(row => row.subscription_active === true);
console.log(`Active Subscribers: ${active.count()}`);

// Total monthly revenue
const revenue = active.sum('monthly_spend');
console.log(`Total Monthly Revenue: $${revenue.toFixed(2)}`);

// Average subscription cost
